        <title>Life&#39;s Hard</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2023/lifes-hard.html</link>
        <pubDate>Fri, 03 Mar 2023 15:03:03 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<h3 id="引">引</h3>
<p>『人生如寄，多忧何为？』</p>
<h3 id="正文">正文</h3>
<p>从来都没想到会有这么一天。<br/>
或许，意外都是在最确信的地方发生。<br/>
同样，我们往往在最值得信任的人那里，丢掉了信任。</p>
<p>回过头来，感觉自己似乎没有任何资格说这样的话。<br/>
从无数的错误中走出来，有些改正了，有些甚至都没有。<br/>
那，凭什么，可以要求别人不能犯错误？</p>
<p>从自己现在的痛苦中，才理解了别人的痛苦。<br/>
果然，只有真正体验了苦痛的人才能了解它有多痛。</p>
<p>那，又为什么这么痛？<br/>
是因为第一次吗？我猜是的吧。<br/>
或者，也有可能是自己太笃定了，从未准备过会有这样的冲击。</p>
<h3 id="忧愁">忧愁</h3>
<p>人生短暂，我们不过寄宿在这个世上。<br/>
如果，真的是这样，我们又为何如此多的忧愁。</p>
<h3 id="快乐">快乐</h3>
<p>『人的行为都是快乐驱使的』<br/>
我曾经很怀疑这句话，因为觉得只有自己是俗人。<br/>
现在，我信了。<br/>
克制和隐忍，都是有尽头的。<br/>
出走，并寻找快乐，才是大家都在做的事情。</p>
<h3 id="最后">最后</h3>
<p>想明白了，又似乎没想明白。<br/>
这，又是一个路口。<br/>
可能真的要停下来好好想想了。</p>]]></description>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">https://seasonsroad.com/post/2023/lifes-hard.html</guid>
      </item><item>
        <title>Enabling NTFS write on macOS 10.15 Catalina</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/enable-ntfs-mac.html</link>
        <pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2020 07:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<blockquote>
<p>Source: <a href="https://medium.com/macoclock/enabling-ntfs-write-in-macos-10-15-catalina-the-open-source-way-a5fd0d1cb32e">Enabling NTFS write in macOS 10.15 Catalina the Open source way</a></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is a good article, and requires little tech knowledge. Copy it here for future reference. Kudos to the original author.</p>
<h1 id="highlighted-steps">Highlighted Steps</h1>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Have <a href="https://developer.apple.com/download/more/">Command Line Tools for Xcode</a> installed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Have <a href="https://brew.sh/">Homebrew package manager</a> installed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Install <a href="https://github.com/osxfuse/osxfuse/releases">FUSE for macOS</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Install package ntfs-3g, <code>brew install ntfs-3g</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Disable System Integrity Protection</p>
</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Restart into Recovery mode by holding <code>Command + R</code> when starting.</li>
<li>Open Terminal application and input command: <code>csrutil disable</code>.</li>
<li>Restart</li>
</ul>
<ol start="6">
<li>Changing the system-wide command <code>mount_ntfs</code></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Mount root folder writable, <code>sudo mount -uw /</code>.</li>
<li>Backup original <code>mount_ntfs</code>, <code>sudo mv /sbin/mount_ntfs /sbin/mount_ntfs.original</code>.</li>
<li>Switch to new <code>mount_ntfs</code>, <code>sudo ln -s /usr/local/sbin/mount_ntfs /sbin/mount_ntfs</code>.</li>
</ul>
<ol start="7">
<li>Re-enable Mac System Integrity Protection</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Restart into Recovery mode again.</li>
<li>Open Terminal application and input command: <code>csrutil enable</code>.</li>
<li>Restart</li>
</ul>
<ol start="8">
<li>Enjoy writing to NTFS!</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>NOTES: Unfortunately, you have to repeat this procedure every time you update to a new major release of macOS. However, it&rsquo;s far better than doing it every restart. :)</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="updates-for-mac-11x-big-sur">Updates for Mac 11.x Big Sur</h2>
<p>We have to use one time set-up now after upgrading to Mac 11.x Big Sur, b/c 1) we can&rsquo;t mount <code>/</code> writable outside recovery mode, and 2) any changes in recovery mode will get reset after reboot.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>List all the disk partitions, <code>diskutil list</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Find the NTFS partition and unmount it, <code>sudo umount /dev/disk2s1</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Create the mount point, <code>sudo mkdir /Volumes/NTFS</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Mount the NTFS partition, <code>sudo /usr/local/bin/ntfs-3g /dev/disk2s1 /Volumes/NTFS -olocal -oallow_other</code></p>
</li>
</ol>]]></description>
