      </item><item>
        <title>Hulu 五周年</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/fifth-huluversary.html</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2020 23:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<p>&ldquo;Give me FIVE!!&rdquo;</p>
<p>五年很长，一个人一生职业生涯不过三十年，我已经走过前六分之一了。况且，也不能指望生涯后半段依然像刚入职那样努力，毕竟精力在下降，能力也在下降。</p>
<p>五年也很短，现在回首看去，依然可以想到很多很多趣事。唯一有点失落的是，想要与人分享时，却发现那只是我自己的记忆。</p>
<br/>
<center><p><img src="/posts/2020/fifth-huluversary/cake.jpg" alt="The Cake" ></p></center>
<p>第一次在 Hulu 收到蛋糕庆祝，还是很感动。因为生日大多在假期中间，一般是收到贺卡。当然这次也收到了贺卡，而且很多张，里面也有不少让人感动的文字。蛋糕上有美队和雷神，想想自己从某种程度上也能成为他们一些人心中的超级英雄，感觉也是有丝丝欣慰。</p>
<p>又想想近况，感觉心里有点苦涩。因为这些不舍的记忆和人，恰恰影响到了这颗想要出逃的心。</p>
<p>一个前同事发来贺电，『5年前的今天也是个周一，你的周年纪念日很有意义』。。想想，其实也是他的周年纪念日，很怀念那段一起打拼的日子，只不过他早已有了新的周年纪念日。</p>
<br/>
<p>最近跟很多人聊，有人想要挽留，有人建议我寻求自我。其实，还是要笃定一些，不是吗？</p>
<p>『围城』，到底还是围了自己。</p>]]></description>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/fifth-huluversary.html</guid>
      </item><item>
        <title>高考延期了</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/ncee-delayed.html</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2020 18:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<p>大多数人都会经历的一件事，就是『高考』。</p>
<p>不排除经历了多次的，比如我，比如我媳妇儿，虽然原因不一样。同样，也不排除没有经历过的。这件事依然是很重要的一件事，对于『大多数人』来说。</p>
<p>就在今年，高考不得不延期了——普遍延期一个月，北京和湖北另行安排。可见，疫情的杀伤力还是相当巨大。</p>
<p>同样，今天还有另外一个消息，迪爸爸高管们都降薪了。一个『帝国』都经受不了的冲击，更何况是我们这些普通人？</p>
<br/>
<p>在顺遂的时候，很多决定都可以很快做下来。但唯独这种时候，需要更加慎重。</p>
<br/>
<p>往好了想，环境影响人，但环境也造就人。<br/>
往坏了想，水能载舟，亦能覆舟。</p>]]></description>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/ncee-delayed.html</guid>
      </item><item>
        <title>关于责任心</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/choice-about-responsibility.html</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 10 Mar 2020 16:10:00 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<p>最近其实处在了一个可能不存在的交叉口上，想到了<a href="/post/2015/crossroads.html">五年前</a>找工作时候的一些有关于抉择的东西，突然有感而发。</p>
<br/>
<p>那时候，事情很简单，选 A 或者 B，尤其是当 B 不再是一个选择的时候。</p>
<p>而现在，事情感觉略略有些复杂。人际关系的构建其实是非常复杂的事情，尤其是对我这种工科生出身的人。真的觉得，如果离开了沉没成本有点太高了，毕竟我珍惜地在这里度过了五年，更不用提现在有很多值得信任又信任我的小伙伴。</p>
<br/>
<p>但是，如果我保持现状，我觉得自己所失去的机会成本大之又大。</p>
<p>所以，我现在面临了这种抉择，需要选择对自己负责，或者对大家负责。</p>
<br/>
<p>但反之又想，是不是我心志太大了，还是只是我心思太重了？</p>
<p>优柔寡断，是一直以来我都没有克服的自身问题。</p>
<br/>
<p>这次，我决定再走一步。至少看下，在已知沉没成本的情况下，机会成本到底有多少。</p>
<p>哪怕，那只是一个预估的数字。<br/>
哪怕，未来还有很多变数。</p>]]></description>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/choice-about-responsibility.html</guid>
      </item><item>
        <title>HEVCify My Camera Videos</title>
        <link>https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/hevcify-camera-videos.html</link>
        <pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2020 00:10:00 +0800</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[<p>I&rsquo;ve been creating camera videos a lot on my Android phone. I usually take 4K videos. However, recently the video has been occupying over 100GB size of total 256G. If I don&rsquo;t fix that, I can store no more things on my OnePlus 7 Pro.</p>
<p>I&rsquo;ve been thinking if I could select some of the videos and delete others. However, even all my videos/photos have backups on my OneDrive, I still need to watch the videos with my family from time to time. So I don&rsquo;t want to delete them.</p>
<p>In my first thought, the solutions could be, 1) buy a new phone 2) NAS / Network Attached Storage. However, my phone is functioning so well that I don&rsquo;t think I could find another phone that could be better (except OP7tPro). And for the second solution, I&rsquo;ve already got a network disk setup, the performance seems okay. However, it seems not okay to use NAS to watch videos. You know, long VST/VRT, high CIRR, and something VPF. 😔</p>
<p>After several months with this pain in my head, a new idea came up to me. How about re-encoding the videos? Actually, I thought about compression. However, it seems not tolerable when the video is not clear any longer&hellip;</p>
<p>Another thought came to me that H.265/HEVC is <em>somehow</em> widely used. How about encode my videos to HEVC as lossless compression? Then I just installed <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.silentlexx.ffmpeggui&amp;hl=en_US">FFmpeg Media Encoder</a> from Google Play, and encoded one of my videos.</p>
<p>And then I was shocked by the result.. A video with 500M size is compressed into 70M. In case the video bit rate is not so good, I compared the videos for almost 10 times. And I don&rsquo;t see difference&hellip; Holly&hellip;</p>
<p>So, let&rsquo;s get started!</p>
<h2 id="on-the-phone">On the Phone</h2>
<h3 id="step-1">Step 1</h3>
<p>Try <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.silentlexx.ffmpeggui&amp;hl=en_US">FFmpeg Media Encoder</a> by your own to see if you could accept the long time for encoding.</p>
<h3 id="step-2">Step 2</h3>
<p>Select videos to encode.</p>
<h3 id="step-3">Step 3</h3>
<p>And you will lose the Exif metadata by default. To restore that, you could either try <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.exiftool.free&amp;hl=en_US">Exiftool</a> or <a href="https://video.stackexchange.com/a/26076">copy tags while encoding</a>.</p>
<h2 id="on-mac">On Mac</h2>
<p>However, It seems not very efficient on phone. Why not use my Mac? With my Mac, I could do more scripting and also I could process the video as a batch.</p>
<h3 id="step-1-1">Step 1</h3>
<p>ADB or Network ADB. <code>brew cask install android-platform-tools</code> to install <code>adb</code>.</p>
<p>For network ADB,</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"># while connecting the phone to mac</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>adb tcpip <span style="color:#ae81ff">5555</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"># network adb connect</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>adb connect 192.168.xxx.xxx:5555
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="step-2-1">Step 2</h3>
<p>Pull the video files to Mac.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span style="display:flex;"><span>adb pull /sdcard/DCIM/Camera/VID_20200202_020202.mp4
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="step-3-1">Step 3</h3>
<p>Encode with <code>ffmpeg</code>. <code>brew install ffmpeg</code> to install <code>ffmpeg</code>.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span style="display:flex;"><span>ffmpeg -i VID_20200202_020202.mp4 -c:v libx265 -c:a aac VID_20200202_020202_HEVC.mp4
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"># if you want to customize the parameters, check the ffmpeg manual.</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>man ffmpeg
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#75715e"># or just</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>ffmpeg
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="step-4">Step 4</h3>
<p>Restore EXIF metadata with <code>exiftool</code> to copy original EXIF tags to the new video file. <code>brew install exiftool</code> to install <code>exiftool</code>.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span style="display:flex;"><span>exiftool -tagsFromFile VID_20200202_020202.mp4 VID_20200202_020202_HEVC.mp4
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="step-5">Step 5</h3>
<p>Send video file back to phone.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span style="display:flex;"><span>adb push VID_20200202_020202_HEVC.mp4 /sdcard/DCIM/
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="step-6">Step 6</h3>
<p>Now compare these two videos.</p>
<h2 id="at-last">At last</h2>
<p>Now, it&rsquo;s been a while since the first encoding. And the result till now is pretty promising. At this moment, I&rsquo;ve got ~500M of videos files encoded from ~5G original video files.</p>]]></description>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">https://seasonsroad.com/post/2020/hevcify-camera-videos.html</guid>
